From: Anders Roxell <anders.roxell@linaro.org>
Date: Sat, 30 Aug 2025 11:49:53 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] dmaengine: ti: edma: Fix memory allocation size for queue_priority_map
Git-commit: e63419dbf2ceb083c1651852209c7f048089ac0f
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc6
References: git-fixes

Fix a critical memory allocation bug in edma_setup_from_hw() where
queue_priority_map was allocated with insufficient memory. The code
declared queue_priority_map as s8 (*)[2] (pointer to array of 2 s8),
but allocated memory using sizeof(s8) instead of the correct size.

This caused out-of-bounds memory writes when accessing:
  queue_priority_map[i][0] = i;
  queue_priority_map[i][1] = i;

The bug manifested as kernel crashes with "Oops - undefined instruction"
on ARM platforms (BeagleBoard-X15) during EDMA driver probe, as the
memory corruption triggered kernel hardening features on Clang.

Change the allocation to use sizeof(*queue_priority_map) which
automatically gets the correct size for the 2D array structure.

Fixes: 2b6b3b742019 ("ARM/dmaengine: edma: Merge the two drivers under drivers/dma/")
Signed-off-by: Anders Roxell <anders.roxell@linaro.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250830094953.3038012-1-anders.roxell@linaro.org
Signed-off-by: Vinod Koul <vkoul@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/dma/ti/edma.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/dma/ti/edma.c b/drivers/dma/ti/edma.c
index 3ed406f08c44..552be71db6c4 100644
--- a/drivers/dma/ti/edma.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/ti/edma.c
@@ -2064,8 +2064,8 @@ static int edma_setup_from_hw(struct device *dev, struct edma_soc_info *pdata,
 	 * priority. So Q0 is the highest priority queue and the last queue has
 	 * the lowest priority.
 	 */
-	queue_priority_map = devm_kcalloc(dev, ecc->num_tc + 1, sizeof(s8),
-					  GFP_KERNEL);
+	queue_priority_map = devm_kcalloc(dev, ecc->num_tc + 1,
+					  sizeof(*queue_priority_map), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!queue_priority_map)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
